JOHANNESBURG - Thursday is Africa Day, and celebrations are expected countrywide. The day, previously known as African Freedom Day and African Liberation Day, is the annual commemoration of the formation of the Organisation of African Unity on 25 May 1963.READ: Ten things you need to know about Africa DayPresident Jacob Zuma will kick off the official commemoration in Pretoria.Zuma says the day provides South Africa with an opportunity to celebrate African solidarity, and to continue supporting African countries that are caught in conflict.Zuma says South Africa will also use Africa Day to recommit itself to the African Union s Agenda 2063, which is a plan to build a better Africa.eNCA